psalm.text:
[[Ps 96,1]]Sing to the LORD a new song; 
sing to the LORD, all you lands.
[[Ps 96,2a]]Sing to the LORD; bless his name.

[[Ps 96,2b]]Announce his salvation, day after day.
[[Ps 96,3]]Tell his glory among the nations;
among all peoples, his wondrous deeds.  

[[Ps 96,7]]Give to the LORD, you families of nations, 
give to the LORD glory and praise;
[[Ps 96,8a]]give to the LORD the glory due his name!

[[Ps 96,9]]Worship the LORD in holy attire. 
Tremble before him, all the earth;
[[Ps 96,10a]]Say among the nations: The LORD is king.
[[Ps 96,10c]]He governs the peoples with equity.

second_reading.text:
[[1_Co 12,4]]Brothers and sisters: There are different kinds of spiritual gifts but the same Spirit;
[[1_Co 12,5]]there are different forms of service but the same Lord;
[[1_Co 12,6]]there are different workings but the same God who produces all of them in everyone.
[[1_Co 12,7]]To each individual the manifestation of the Spirit is given for some benefit.
[[1_Co 12,8]]To one is given through the Spirit the expression of wisdom; to another the expression of knowledge according to the same Spirit;
[[1_Co 12,9]]to another faith by the same Spirit; to another gifts of healing by the one Spirit;
[[1_Co 12,10]]to another mighty deeds; to another prophecy; to another discernment of spirits; to another varieties of tongues; to another interpretation of tongues.
[[1_Co 12,11]]But one and the same Spirit produces all of these, distributing them individually to each person as he wishes.
